'Mohammed V International Airport' (; , ) is an airport serving Casablanca,
operated by ONDA (National Airports Office). Located in the Nouaceur Province,
it is the busiest airport in Morocco, with a traffic of almost 7.25 million
passengers passing through the airport in 2010. |publisher= Office Nationale des AÃ©roports|url= http://www.onda.ma/NR/rdonlyres/7E254108-9D67-48EE-9191-
B05CDC5E642A/1621/communiqu%C3%A9traficdecembre.pdf|archiveurl=
http://www.webcitation.org/6DqVjXDQf|archivedate= }} ONDA informed an
increase of 6.9% for passenger traffic in ; this month, the number of passengers
handled was 634,690. |archiveurl=http://www.webcitation.org/6ICbvPN3h|archi-
vedate=}}

The airport serves as hub for Morocco's flag carrier Royal Air Maroc, Jetairfly,
Air Arabia Maroc and RAM Express. It was named after King Mohammed V of Morocco.
